      "paragraph_name": "1200-SCHEDULE-PSB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph schedules a PSB (Program Specification Block) for IMS database access. It executes a DLI SCHD command with the PSB-NAME and NODHABEND option. The DIBSTAT is moved to IMS-RETURN-CODE. If the PSB is scheduled more than once, it terminates the PSB and schedules it again. If the status is OK, it sets IMS-PSB-SCHD to TRUE. Otherwise, it logs an error using 9500-LOG-ERROR, setting various error fields and flags.",
