      "paragraph_name": "9100-CLOSE-REQUEST-QUEUE",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph closes the request message queue. It checks if the request message queue is open (WS-REQUEST-MQ-OPEN). If it is, it calls the MQCLOSE program to close the queue, passing the connection handle (W01-HCONN-REQUEST), object handle (W01-HOBJ-REQUEST), and other parameters. It then checks the completion code (WS-COMPCODE). If the close operation is successful (MQCC-OK), it sets WS-REQUEST-MQ-CLSE to TRUE. If the close operation fails, it logs an error using 9500-LOG-ERROR.",
